{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RmTRSciNZ4m4Rj6YrMRu8q","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-ralph-driver-implementation.md`\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 3 Medium, 3 Low\n\n## CRITICAL/HIGH Issues (Fixed)\n\n1. **HIGH: `tool-complete` AgentEvent carried fake empty `name`/`args` strings** (ralph.ts:237) -- The `parseOutput()` method mapped `StreamEvent.tool-complete` to `{ type: 'tool-complete', name: '', args: '' }`. The stream parser is stateless and cannot know the tool name/args at block-stop time. Fixed by making `name`/`args` optional in the `AgentEvent` type (types.ts:40) and emitting `{ type: 'tool-complete' }` without fake data. Added test coverage for this case.\n\n2. **HIGH (downgraded to MEDIUM after analysis): Missing `spawn()` test coverage** -- AC16 requires tests for `spawn()` arg building. The test file had zero tests for `RalphDriver.spawn()`. Fixed by adding 5 tests that mock `node:child_process` and verify: bash invocation, prompt arg passthrough, timeout passthrough, env merging, and return type.\n\n## MEDIUM Issues (Fixed)\n\n3. **MEDIUM: No tool-complete delegation test** -- The stream-json delegation section tested tool-start, text, result, retry, and tool-input, but never tool-complete. Added a test verifying tool-complete events arrive without name/args properties.\n\n## Files Changed During Review\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/types.ts` -- Made `name`/`args` optional on `tool-complete` variant\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` -- Removed fake empty strings from tool-complete mapping\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph.test.ts` -- Added 6 new tests (5 spawn, 1 tool-complete delegation)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-ralph-driver-implementation.md` -- Status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Test Results\n\n- 3606 tests pass (3600 before + 6 new)\n- 97.08% overall coverage, all 153 files above 80% floor\n- Zero TypeScript errors in story-related files\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: `tool-complete` AgentEvent emitted fabricated empty `name`/`args` strings -- FIXED\n- MEDIUM: Zero test coverage for `RalphDriver.spawn()` method -- FIXED\n- MEDIUM: No tool-complete delegation test in stream-json test section -- FIXED\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority, tech debt):**\n- LOW: `RalphDriver.spawn()` hardcodes `maxIterations=50`, `iterationTimeout=30`, `calls=100`, `quiet=false` because `SpawnOpts` doesn't carry these fields. This means the driver interface cannot fully replace the direct `buildSpawnArgs()` call in `run.ts`. This is by design for now (story 13-3 will refactor run.ts to use the driver), but the `SpawnOpts` interface will need expansion.\n- LOW: `resolveRalphPath()` uses string suffix check (`endsWith('/src')`) which is fragile on Windows. Not a current concern since the tool targets macOS/Linux.\n- LOW: `retry` event from ralph stderr `[WARN] Story {key} -- retry N/M` drops the story key because `AgentEvent.retry` has no `key` field. Consumers cannot tell which story is being retried. This is a types.ts design gap to address in a future story.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All files pass 80% per-file minimum and 97.08% overall.\n- Edge case: `resolveRalphPath()` is not unit tested in isolation (it depends on `import.meta.url`). Tested indirectly via spawn() tests.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `RalphDriver.spawn()` method duplicates parameter knowledge that also exists in `run.ts` action handler. Story 13-3 should eliminate this duplication by having `run.ts` use the driver exclusively.\n- `createLineProcessor` in `run-helpers.ts` imports `parseRalphMessage` and `parseIterationMessage` from `agents/ralph.ts`, creating a reverse dependency (run-helpers depends on agents). This coupling should be resolved when 13-3 refactors `run.ts` to use `AgentDriver.parseOutput()` directly.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:** None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1dc4205863cfa3b0 (use SendMessage with to: 'a1dc4205863cfa3b0' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 94292\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 256198</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"d8bd9a55-ab0c-4ecf-8cc7-1b3b469574e4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:10:09.790Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-ralph-driver-implementation.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a1dc4205863cfa3b0","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-ralph-driver-implementation.md`\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 3 Medium, 3 Low\n\n## CRITICAL/HIGH Issues (Fixed)\n\n1. **HIGH: `tool-