{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MXmamp1CmXoGn6cc84fn2K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-3: Migrate run.ts to Use AgentDriver\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want `run.ts` to use `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning Ralph,\n     9→So that the run command is agent-agnostic.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it imports `AgentDriver` and calls `driver.spawn()`, not `spawn('bash', [ralphPath, ...])` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `resolveRalphPath()` in run.ts, when migration completes, then it's moved into `ralph.ts` and run.ts uses `driver.getExecutablePath()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction).** The run command becomes agent-agnostic by programming to the `AgentDriver` interface.\n    19→\n    20→Current `src/commands/run.ts` directly:\n    21→- Imports `spawn` from `child_process`\n    22→- Calls `resolveRalphPath()` to find ralph.sh\n    23→- Builds args array specific to ralph.sh flags\n    24→- Parses ralph's stderr for iteration/status messages\n    25→- Reads `ralph/status.json` for session results\n    26→\n    27→After migration:\n    28→```typescript\n    29→// src/commands/run.ts\n    30→import { getRalphDriver } from '../lib/agents/index.js';\n    31→import type { AgentDriver, AgentEvent } from '../lib/agents/types.js';\n    32→\n    33→// In the run action:\n    34→const driver: AgentDriver = getRalphDriver();\n    35→const process = driver.spawn({\n    36→  storyKey,\n    37→  prompt,\n    38→  workDir: projectDir,\n    39→  timeout: sessionTimeout,\n    40→  env: { OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT: endpoint }\n    41→});\n    42→\n    43→process.stderr.on('data', (chunk) => {\n    44→  const event = driver.parseOutput(chunk.toString());\n    45→  if (event) handleAgentEvent(event);\n    46→});\n    47→\n    48→process.on('close', (code) => {\n    49→  // Read results from driver.getStatusFile()\n    50→});\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→The `handleAgentEvent()` function replaces the current inline parsing. It switches on `event.type` and updates the Ink renderer or sprint state accordingly.\n    54→\n    55→A factory function `getDriver(name?: string): AgentDriver` in `src/lib/agents/index.ts` defaults to `RalphDriver`. Future drivers can be selected via CLI flag `--agent`.\n    56→\n    57→## Files to Change\n    58→\n    59→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Replace direct ralph spawning with `AgentDriver` interface calls. Remove `resolveRalphPath()` import. Add `handleAgentEvent()` dispatcher\n    60→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Add `getDriver()` factory function that returns `RalphDriver` by default\n    61→- `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` — Ensure `resolveRalphPath()` is exposed or used internally by `spawn()`\n    62→- `src/commands/run.ts` imports — Update from `run-helpers.ts` to `agents/index.ts`\n    63→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014LQotcmHZgHHY5F784aj9H","session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"89c5003b-9932-4b8e-8597-0f443abebe74","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:15:00.516Z"}
