{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CxpT5JRzmicFtYyfA5dYPv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-2: Implement RalphDriver\n     2→\n     3→## Status: done\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want Ralph wrapped in an `AgentDriver` implementation,\n    13→So that ralph-specific behavior is isolated in one file.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` exists, when inspected, then it exports a `RalphDriver` class implementing `AgentDriver` with `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, and `getStatusFile()` methods <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given `RalphDriver.spawn()`, when called with valid `SpawnOpts`, then it builds the ralph.sh args array (equivalent to current `buildSpawnArgs()`) and spawns a child process returning an `AgentProcess` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given `RalphDriver.parseOutput()`, when called with a ralph stderr line like `[SUCCESS] Story 1-1-foo: DONE`, then it returns the appropriate `AgentEvent` (e.g., `{ type: 'story-complete', key: '1-1-foo', details: 'DONE' }`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given `RalphDriver.parseOutput()`, when called with a `[LOOP] iteration N` line, then it returns `{ type: 'iteration', count: N }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given `RalphDriver.parseOutput()`, when called with a stream-json NDJSON line, then it delegates to the stream parser and returns the corresponding `AgentEvent` or null <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `RalphDriver.getStatusFile()`, when called, then it returns `'ralph/status.json'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` absorbs `parseRalphMessage()`, `parseIterationMessage()`, and `buildSpawnArgs()` from `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`, when migration completes, then those functions are no longer exported from `run-helpers.ts` and all callers import from `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` instead <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `src/lib/stream-parser.ts`, when migration completes, then it is moved to `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` and all import paths across the codebase are updated <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts`, when migration completes, then it is moved to `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` and all import paths are updated <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`, when migration completes, then it contains only non-ralph-specific functions (`formatElapsed`, `mapSprintStatus`, `mapSprintStatuses`, `countStories`, `createLineProcessor`) OR is deleted if all functions have been migrated <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→11. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts`, when inspected, then it re-exports `RalphDriver`, stream parser types/functions, and ralph prompt types/functions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→12. Given `src/index.ts` exports `parseStreamLine` and stream event types, when the stream parser moves to `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts`, then `src/index.ts` import paths are updated and the public API is unchanged <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    29→13. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→14. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    31→15. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    32→16. Given `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph.test.ts` exists, when inspected, then it tests `RalphDriver.parseOutput()` for all ralph stderr patterns (success, retry, retry-exceeded, error, iteration) and stream-json delegation, plus `getStatusFile()` and `spawn()` arg building <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    33→\n    34→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    35→\n    36→- [x]Task 1 (AC: 8, 12): Move `src/lib/stream-parser.ts` to `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts`\n    37→  - [x]Move the file\n    38→  - [x]Update all imports across the codebase: `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`, `src/index.ts`, `src/__tests__/run-pipeline.test.ts`, `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`, `src/lib/__tests__/stream-parser.test.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx`\n    39→  - [x]Move `src/lib/__tests__/stream-parser.test.ts` to `src/lib/agents/__tests__/stream-parser.test.ts`\n    40→  - [x]Verify `src/index.ts` public API still exports `parseStreamLine` and all `StreamEvent` types\n    41→\n    42→- [x]Task 2 (AC: 9): Move `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` to `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts`\n    43→  - [x]Move the file\n    44→  - [x]Update imports: `src/commands/run.ts`\n    45→  - [x]Move `src/templates/__tests__/ralph-prompt.test.ts` to `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph-prompt.test.ts`\n    46→\n    47→- [x]Task 3 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 10): Create `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` implementing `RalphDriver`\n    48→  - [x]Import `AgentDriver`, `SpawnOpts`, `AgentProcess`, `AgentEvent` from `./types.js`\n    49→  - [x]Migrate `buildSpawnArgs()` from `run-helpers.ts` into ralph.ts (as private method or module-level function)\n    50→  - [x]Migrate `parseRalphMessage()` and `parseIterationMessage()` from `run-helpers.ts` into ralph.ts\n    51→  - [x]Add `resolveRalphPath()` from `run.ts` into ralph.ts\n    52→  - [x]Implement `spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess` — builds args via `buildSpawnArgs`, spawns `bash ralph.sh`\n    53→  - [x]Implement `parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null` — tries ralph stderr patterns first, falls back to stream-json parser, maps internal types to `AgentEvent`\n    54→  - [x]Implement `getStatusFile(): string` — returns `'ralph/status.json'`\n    55→  - [x]Export `RalphDriver` class and re-export migrated functions for backward compatibility\n    56→\n    57→- [x]Task 4 (AC: 7, 10): Clean up `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`\n    58→  - [x]Remove `parseRalphMessage()`, `parseIterationMessage()`, `buildSpawnArgs()` and their regex constants\n    59→  - [x]Remove the `import { parseStreamLine } from './stream-parser.js'` (file moved)\n    60→  - [x]Update `createLineProcessor` to import from new locations\n    61→  - [x]Keep `formatElapsed`, `mapSprintStatus`, `mapSprintStatuses`, `countStories`, `createLineProcessor` — these are run-command helpers, not ralph-specific\n    62→  - [x]Update `src/commands/run.ts` to import `buildSpawnArgs` from `../lib/agents/ralph.js` and `resolveRalphPath` from same\n    63→\n    64→- [x]Task 5 (AC: 11): Update `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n    65→  - [x]Re-export `RalphDriver` from `./ralph.js`\n    66→  - [x]Re-export stream parser functions and types from `./stream-parser.js`\n    67→  - [x]Re-export ralph prompt functions and types from `./ralph-prompt.js`\n    68→\n    69→- [x]Task 6 (AC: 16): Create `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph.test.ts`\n    70→  - [x]Test `parseOutput()` with `[SUCCESS] Story ...` lines → `story-complete` events\n    71→  - [x]Test `parseOutput()` with `[WARN] Story ... exceeded retry limit` → `story-failed` events\n    72→  - [x]Test `parseOutput()` with `[WARN] Story ... retry N/M` → `retry` events\n    73→  - [x]Test `parseOutput()` with `[LOOP] iteration N` → `iteration` events\n    74→  - [x]Test `parseOutput()` with stream-json NDJSON lines → delegated events\n    75→  - [x]Test `parseOutput()` with unrecognized lines → null\n    76→  - [x]Test `getStatusFile()` returns `'ralph/status.json'`\n    77→  - [x]Test `buildSpawnArgs()` via unit tests (migrated from run-helpers.test.ts or new)\n    78→  - [x]Test `name` property equals `'ralph'`\n    79→\n    80→- [x]Task 7 (AC: 13): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    81→- [x]Task 8 (AC: 14): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    82→- [x]Task 9 (AC: 15): Verify all new files in `src/lib/agents/` are under 300 lines\n    83→\n    84→## Dev Notes\n    85→\n    86→### Architecture Compliance\n    87→\n    88→- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This story creates the first concrete `AgentDriver` implementation. `RalphDriver` wraps `ralph.sh` invocation behind the interface defined in story 13-1.\n    89→- **Decision 4 (Domain Subdirectories):** All ralph-related code moves under `src/lib/agents/`. The stream parser and ralph prompt template also relocate here.\n    90→- **300-line limit (Decision 7, NFR5):** `ralph.ts` will absorb ~130 lines from `run-helpers.ts` (ralph-specific functions) plus ~30 lines for the class shell. Target: ~170 lines. Stream parser stays at 193 lines. Ralph prompt stays at 84 lines. All well under 300.\n    91→\n    92→### Implementation Guidance\n    93→\n    94→**RalphDriver class shape:**\n    95→\n    96→```typescript\n    97→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n    98→import type { AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent } from './types.js';\n    99→import { parseStreamLine } from './stream-parser.js';\n   100→\n   101→export class RalphDriver implements AgentDriver {\n   102→  readonly name = 'ralph';\n   103→\n   104→  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess {\n   105→    const args = buildSpawnArgs({ /* map SpawnOpts to buildSpawnArgs format */ });\n   106→    const child = spawn('bash', args, {\n   107→      cwd: opts.workDir,\n   108→      env: { ...process.env, ...opts.env },\n   109→      stdio: ['inherit', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n   110→    });\n   111→    return child as unknown as AgentProcess;\n   112→  }\n   113→\n   114→  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null {\n   115→    // 1. Try ralph stderr patterns (story-complete, story-failed, iteration, retry)\n   116→    // 2. Fall back to stream-json parser\n   117→    // 3. Map internal types to AgentEvent discriminated union\n   118→  }\n   119→\n   120→  getStatusFile(): string {\n   121→    return 'ralph/status.json';\n   122→  }\n   123→}\n   124→```\n   125→\n   126→**Type mapping in `parseOutput()`:**\n   127→\n   128→The existing `parseRalphMessage()` returns `StoryMessage` with `type: 'ok' | 'fail' | 'warn'`. The `AgentEvent` uses different discriminants. Mapping:\n   129→\n   130→- `StoryMessage { type: 'ok' }` → `AgentEvent { type: 'story-complete', key, details }`\n   131→- `StoryMessage { type: 'fail' }` → `AgentEvent { type: 'story-failed', key, reason }`\n   132→- `StoryMessage { type: 'warn' }` → `AgentEvent { type: 'retry', attempt, delay }` (parse retry N/M from message)\n   133→- `parseIterationMessage()` returns number → `AgentEvent { type: 'iteration', count }`\n   134→- `parseStreamLine()` returns `StreamEvent` → map to corresponding `AgentEvent` variants\n   135→\n   136→**Note on `createLineProcessor()`:** This function stays in `run-helpers.ts` for now. It calls `parseStreamLine()` and `parseRalphMessage()`, so its imports will need updating. Story 13-3 will refactor `run.ts` to use `AgentDriver` directly, which may obsolete `createLineProcessor`.\n   137→\n   138→**Note on backward compatibility:** `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` currently re-exports functions that `run.ts` and test files import. After migration:\n   139→- `buildSpawnArgs` moves to `ralph.ts` — update `run.ts` import\n   140→- `parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage` move to `ralph.ts` — update `createLineProcessor` and test imports\n   141→- `run-helpers.ts` keeps: `formatElapsed`, `mapSprintStatus`, `mapSprintStatuses`, `countStories`, `createLineProcessor`\n   142→- `run.ts` re-exports `countStories`, `buildSpawnArgs` — update the re-export source for `buildSpawnArgs`\n   143→\n   144→**Files that import from `stream-parser.ts` (must update paths):**\n   145→- `src/index.ts` (lines 27-28)\n   146→- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` (lines 10-11)\n   147→- `src/__tests__/run-pipeline.test.ts` (lines 19-20)\n   148→- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` (line 13)\n   149→- `src/lib/__tests__/stream-parser.test.ts` (lines 2, 11)\n   150→- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` (line 6)\n   151→\n   152→**Files that import from `ralph-prompt.ts` (must update paths):**\n   153→- `src/commands/run.ts` (line 8)\n   154→- `src/templates/__tests__/ralph-prompt.test.ts` (line 2)\n   155→\n   156→### Testing Guidance\n   157→\n   158→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   159→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`\n   160→- Import convention: use `.js` extension for ESM resolution (e.g., `from '../ralph.js'`).\n   161→- Mock `node:child_process` `spawn` for `RalphDriver.spawn()` tests — verify args passed to spawn, not actual process creation.\n   162→- Existing `run-helpers.test.ts` tests for `buildSpawnArgs`, `parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage` should be migrated to `ralph.test.ts` or updated to import from the new location.\n   163→- `stream-parser.test.ts` moves as-is to `agents/__tests__/` — only import path changes.\n   164→\n   165→### Previous Story Intelligence (13-1)\n   166→\n   167→- Story 13-1 completed. Types are at `src/lib/agents/types.ts`. All 3561 tests passing.\n   168→- `AgentProcess` has both `'close'` and `'error'` event overloads (the `'error'` was an addition beyond spec).\n   169→- `AgentEvent` discriminated union covers 8 types: `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `story-complete`, `story-failed`, `iteration`, `retry`, `result`.\n   170→- Test pattern established in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/types.test.ts` — follow same style.\n   171→\n   172→### Project Structure After This Story\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→src/lib/agents/\n   176→├── types.ts              # AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent (from 13-1)\n   177→├── ralph.ts              # RalphDriver implementation + migrated ralph functions\n   178→├── stream-parser.ts      # Moved from src/lib/stream-parser.ts\n   179→├── ralph-prompt.ts       # Moved from src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts\n   180→├── index.ts              # Re-export facade (updated)\n   181→└── __tests__/\n   182→    ├── types.test.ts     # From 13-1\n   183→    ├── ralph.test.ts     # New: RalphDriver unit tests\n   184→    ├── stream-parser.test.ts  # Moved from src/lib/__tests__/\n   185→    └── ralph-prompt.test.ts   # Moved from src/templates/__tests__/\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→### References\n   189→\n   190→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md lines 255-289] — Epic 13 (Agent Abstraction) stories\n   191→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types.md] — Story 13-1 completion notes\n   192→- [Source: src/lib/run-helpers.ts] — Functions to migrate: `buildSpawnArgs`, `parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage`\n   193→- [Source: src/lib/stream-parser.ts] — File to move to agents/\n   194→- [Source: src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts] — File to move to agents/\n   195→- [Source: src/commands/run.ts] — Primary consumer, `resolveRalphPath()` to migrate\n   196→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014LQotcmHZgHHY5F784aj9H","session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"ec7961a3-b257-4e51-8d8b-06192133039f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:15:01.780Z"}
