{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014LQotcmHZgHHY5F784aj9H","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver.md`.\n\n**Summary of what was created:**\n\n- 13 acceptance criteria, all tagged `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` (every AC is verifiable by inspecting source files or running `npm run build`/`npm test` in a subprocess -- no workflow, sprint planning, user session, or external system interactions)\n- 7 tasks covering: extending RalphDriver.spawn() config, adding getDriver() factory, refactoring run.ts, updating tests, build/test verification, and line count check\n- Dev notes with implementation guidance on the SpawnOpts extension challenge (recommends constructor config pattern), handleAgentEvent() dispatcher shape, createLineProcessor disposition, and ralph existence check strategy\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic AC says `run.ts uses driver.getExecutablePath()` but `AgentDriver` interface (from 13-1) has no `getExecutablePath()` method. The intent is that the executable path is encapsulated inside `driver.spawn()` so run.ts never needs it. I wrote AC3 to reflect the actual interface rather than the stale epic text.\n- **SpawnOpts mismatch:** The `SpawnOpts` interface from 13-1 only has 5 fields (`storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env`), but `run.ts` passes 10+ options to `buildSpawnArgs()`. The story documents this tension and recommends constructor-time configuration for ralph-specific options. This is a design decision the dev will need to make.\n- **RalphDriver.spawn() hardcodes values:** The current `RalphDriver.spawn()` (from 13-2) hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false`. This must be fixed before run.ts can delegate to it, making Task 1 a prerequisite for Task 3.\n- **createLineProcessor disposition unclear:** `createLineProcessor` does line buffering + parsing. After migration, run.ts won't use it, but it's unclear if any other consumer does. The story leaves this as \"possibly remove\" rather than mandating deletion.\n- **Re-export breakage risk:** `run.ts` line 22 re-exports `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath`. If external consumers import these from `codeharness/commands/run`, removing the re-exports is a breaking change. The story flags this but the risk is low (these are internal utilities)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac381d7703303e9a8 (use SendMessage with to: 'ac381d7703303e9a8' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 45122\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 147867</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"528919c0-3d89-4642-8193-eeb29e6efc54","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:17:18.622Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ac381d7703303e9a8","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver.md`.\n\n**Summary of what was created:**\n\n- 13 acceptance criteria, all tagged `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` (every AC is verifiable by inspecting source files or running `npm run build`/`npm test` in a subprocess -- no workflow, sprint planning, user session, or external system interactions)\n- 7 tasks covering: extending RalphDriver.spawn() config, adding getDriver() factory, refactoring run.ts, updating tests, build/test verification, and line count check\n- Dev notes with implementation guidance on the SpawnOpts extension challenge (recommends constructor config pattern), handleAgentEvent() dispatcher shape, createLineProcessor disposition, and ralph existence check strategy\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** The epic AC says `run.ts uses driver.getExecutablePath()` but `AgentDriver` interface (from 13-1) has no `getExecutablePath()` method. The intent is that the executable path is encapsulated inside `driver.spawn()` so run.ts never needs it. I wrote AC3 to reflect the actual interface rather than the stale epic text.\n- **SpawnOpts mismatch:** The `SpawnOpts` interface from 13-1 only has 5 fields (`storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env`), but `run.ts` passes 10+ options to `buildSpawnArgs()`. The story documents this tension and recommends constructor-time configuration for ralph-specific options. This is a design decision the dev will need to make.\n- **RalphDriver.spawn() hardcodes values:** The current `RalphDriver.spawn()` (from 13-2) hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false`. This must be fixed before run.ts can delegate to it, making Task 1 a prerequisite for Task 3.\n- **createLineProcessor disposition unclear:** `createLineProcessor` does line buffering + parsing. After migration, run.ts won't use it, but it's unclear if any other consumer does. The story leaves this as \"possibly remove\" rather than mandating deletion.\n- **Re-export breakage risk:** `run.ts` line 22 re-exports `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath`. If external consumers import these from `codeharness/commands/run`, removing the re-exports is a breaking change. The story flags this but the risk is low (these are internal utilities)."}],"totalDurationMs":147867,"totalTokens":45122,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4471,"cache_read_input_tokens":40024,"output_tokens":626,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4471},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
