{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1qVciTjwb8woVEnrYAFaX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 13-3: Migrate run.ts to Use AgentDriver\n     2→\n     3→## Status: ready-for-dev\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     8→\n     9→## Story\n    10→\n    11→As a developer,\n    12→I want `run.ts` to use `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning Ralph,\n    13→So that the run command is agent-agnostic.\n    14→\n    15→## Acceptance Criteria\n    16→\n    17→1. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it does NOT import `spawn` from `node:child_process` — all process spawning goes through `AgentDriver.spawn()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→2. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it imports a `getDriver()` factory from `../lib/agents/index.js` and calls `driver.spawn(opts)` where `driver` is an `AgentDriver` instance <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→3. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it does NOT import or call `buildSpawnArgs()` or `resolveRalphPath()` directly — those are encapsulated inside `RalphDriver.spawn()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→4. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then it replaces the inline `createLineProcessor` stderr/stdout wiring with `driver.parseOutput(line)` calls that return `AgentEvent` objects, and a `handleAgentEvent()` dispatcher function that updates the Ink renderer <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→5. Given `src/commands/run.ts`, when inspected, then the hardcoded `'ralph/status.json'` path is replaced with `driver.getStatusFile()` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→6. Given `src/lib/agents/index.ts`, when inspected, then it exports a `getDriver(name?: string): AgentDriver` factory function that returns a `RalphDriver` instance by default and throws for unknown driver names <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→7. Given `RalphDriver.spawn()`, when called, then it internally calls `resolveRalphPath()` and `buildSpawnArgs()` — the `SpawnOpts` interface carries enough information for `RalphDriver` to construct all ralph.sh flags (the interface or `spawn()` signature may need extending to pass `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→8. Given `src/commands/run.ts` re-exports `countStories` and `buildSpawnArgs`, when migration completes, then `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath` are no longer re-exported from `run.ts` (they are implementation details of `RalphDriver`) — `countStories` may still be re-exported if external consumers need it <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→9. Given `src/lib/run-helpers.ts`, when inspected, then `createLineProcessor` is either removed (if no longer used) or remains as a backward-compatible utility — run.ts itself must NOT use it <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→10. Given `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`, when inspected, then it tests the run command through the `AgentDriver` interface: mocking `getDriver()` to return a mock driver, verifying `driver.spawn()` is called with correct opts, and verifying `driver.parseOutput()` events are dispatched to the renderer <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→11. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→12. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    29→13. Given no file in `src/lib/agents/` or `src/commands/`, when line count is checked, then no file exceeds 300 lines <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→\n    31→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    32→\n    33→- [ ] Task 1 (AC: 7): Extend `RalphDriver.spawn()` to accept full run configuration\n    34→  - [ ] Extend `SpawnOpts` or add a `RalphSpawnOpts` that includes `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset` fields needed by `buildSpawnArgs()`\n    35→  - [ ] Update `RalphDriver.spawn()` to use these new fields instead of hardcoded defaults (currently hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false`)\n    36→  - [ ] Ensure `resolveRalphPath()` is called internally by `spawn()` — the caller should NOT need to know about `ralph.sh`\n    37→\n    38→- [ ] Task 2 (AC: 6): Add `getDriver()` factory to `src/lib/agents/index.ts`\n    39→  - [ ] Implement `getDriver(name?: string): AgentDriver` — defaults to `'ralph'`, returns `new RalphDriver()`\n    40→  - [ ] Throw a descriptive error for unrecognized driver names (e.g., `Unknown agent driver: ${name}`)\n    41→  - [ ] Export `getDriver` from the barrel\n    42→\n    43→- [ ] Task 3 (AC: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 8, 9): Refactor `src/commands/run.ts`\n    44→  - [ ] Remove `import { spawn } from 'node:child_process'`\n    45→  - [ ] Remove `import { buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath } from '../lib/agents/ralph.js'`\n    46→  - [ ] Add `import { getDriver } from '../lib/agents/index.js'`\n    47→  - [ ] Add `import type { AgentDriver, AgentEvent } from '../lib/agents/types.js'`\n    48→  - [ ] Replace `const ralphPath = resolveRalphPath(); if (!existsSync(ralphPath))` check with driver validation (the driver itself knows if its executable exists)\n    49→  - [ ] Replace `const args = buildSpawnArgs(...)` + `spawn('bash', args, ...)` with `const driver = getDriver(); const child = driver.spawn(opts)`\n    50→  - [ ] Create a `handleAgentEvent(event: AgentEvent, rendererHandle)` function that switches on `event.type` and calls appropriate renderer methods (`update`, `addMessage`, etc.)\n    51→  - [ ] Replace `createLineProcessor` usage with a line splitter that calls `driver.parseOutput(line)` and dispatches via `handleAgentEvent()`\n    52→  - [ ] Replace hardcoded `join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'status.json')` with `join(projectDir, driver.getStatusFile())`\n    53→  - [ ] Remove re-exports of `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath` — keep `countStories` re-export\n    54→  - [ ] Remove the `// resolveRalphPath moved to ...` comment (now fully encapsulated)\n    55→\n    56→- [ ] Task 4 (AC: 10): Update `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`\n    57→  - [ ] Mock `../lib/agents/index.js` to return a mock `AgentDriver` from `getDriver()`\n    58→  - [ ] Remove mocks for `node:child_process` `spawn` (no longer directly called by run.ts)\n    59→  - [ ] Verify `driver.spawn()` is called with the correct `SpawnOpts` when the run command executes\n    60→  - [ ] Verify `driver.parseOutput()` is called for each output line\n    61→  - [ ] Verify `driver.getStatusFile()` is used for reading session results\n    62→  - [ ] Update any tests that reference `buildSpawnArgs` or `resolveRalphPath` imports from run.ts\n    63→\n    64→- [ ] Task 5 (AC: 11): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    65→- [ ] Task 6 (AC: 12): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    66→- [ ] Task 7 (AC: 13): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n    67→\n    68→## Dev Notes\n    69→\n    70→### Architecture Compliance\n    71→\n    72→- **Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction):** This is the capstone story of Epic 13. After this, `run.ts` programs exclusively to the `AgentDriver` interface. Swapping Ralph for another agent requires only a new driver implementation and a `getDriver('newagent')` call.\n    73→- **Decision 7 (300-line limit, NFR5):** `run.ts` is currently 282 lines. The refactoring should reduce it slightly (removing inline buildSpawnArgs/resolveRalphPath usage), but the `handleAgentEvent()` function adds some code. Monitor the total.\n    74→\n    75→### Implementation Guidance\n    76→\n    77→**The core change pattern:**\n    78→\n    79→```typescript\n    80→// BEFORE (current run.ts):\n    81→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n    82→import { buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath } from '../lib/agents/ralph.js';\n    83→// ...\n    84→const ralphPath = resolveRalphPath();\n    85→const args = buildSpawnArgs({ ralphPath, pluginDir, promptFile, ... });\n    86→const child = spawn('bash', args, { stdio, cwd, env });\n    87→// ...\n    88→const stdoutHandler = createLineProcessor({ onEvent: ... });\n    89→const stderrHandler = createLineProcessor({ onEvent: ..., onMessage: ..., onIteration: ... }, { parseRalph: true });\n    90→child.stdout.on('data', stdoutHandler);\n    91→child.stderr.on('data', stderrHandler);\n    92→// ...\n    93→const statusFile = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'status.json');\n    94→\n    95→// AFTER:\n    96→import { getDriver } from '../lib/agents/index.js';\n    97→import type { AgentDriver, AgentEvent } from '../lib/agents/types.js';\n    98→// ...\n    99→const driver = getDriver();\n   100→const child = driver.spawn({ storyKey: '...', prompt: promptFile, workDir: projectDir, timeout, ... });\n   101→// ...\n   102→// Line splitting + driver.parseOutput() + handleAgentEvent()\n   103→// ...\n   104→const statusFile = join(projectDir, driver.getStatusFile());\n   105→```\n   106→\n   107→**SpawnOpts extension challenge:**\n   108→\n   109→The current `SpawnOpts` interface (from 13-1) has: `storyKey`, `prompt`, `workDir`, `timeout`, `env`. But `run.ts` passes many more options to `buildSpawnArgs()`: `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset`.\n   110→\n   111→Options for handling this:\n   112→1. **Extend `SpawnOpts`** with optional ralph-specific fields (violates interface purity)\n   113→2. **Use `env` bag** to pass extra config (hacky)\n   114→3. **Add a `RalphSpawnOpts extends SpawnOpts`** type that `RalphDriver.spawn()` accepts (type-safe, recommended)\n   115→4. **Configure `RalphDriver` at construction time** — pass ralph-specific options to the constructor, leaving `SpawnOpts` generic\n   116→\n   117→Option 3 or 4 is recommended. Option 4 is cleanest: `new RalphDriver(ralphConfig)` at construction, then `driver.spawn(genericOpts)` at call time. This keeps `SpawnOpts` agent-agnostic.\n   118→\n   119→**handleAgentEvent() dispatcher:**\n   120→\n   121→```typescript\n   122→function handleAgentEvent(\n   123→  event: AgentEvent,\n   124→  rendererHandle: RendererHandle,\n   125→  state: { currentIterationCount: number },\n   126→): void {\n   127→  switch (event.type) {\n   128→    case 'tool-start':\n   129→    case 'tool-complete':\n   130→    case 'text':\n   131→    case 'result':\n   132→    case 'retry':\n   133→      // Map to StreamEvent-like shape for renderer.update()\n   134→      rendererHandle.update(event);\n   135→      break;\n   136→    case 'story-complete':\n   137→      rendererHandle.addMessage({ type: 'ok', key: event.key, message: event.details });\n   138→      break;\n   139→    case 'story-failed':\n   140→      rendererHandle.addMessage({ type: 'fail', key: event.key, message: event.reason });\n   141→      break;\n   142→    case 'iteration':\n   143→      state.currentIterationCount = event.count;\n   144→      break;\n   145→  }\n   146→}\n   147→```\n   148→\n   149→**Note on `createLineProcessor`:** The line-splitting logic (buffering partial lines across chunk boundaries, splitting on `\\n`) is generic and useful. It can stay in `run-helpers.ts` as a utility OR be inlined in run.ts. The key change is that `createLineProcessor`'s internal calls to `parseStreamLine()` and `parseRalphMessage()` are replaced by `driver.parseOutput()`.\n   150→\n   151→**Ralph existence check:** Currently run.ts does `if (!existsSync(ralphPath))`. After migration, the driver should handle this. Options:\n   152→- Add a `validate(): boolean` method to `AgentDriver` interface\n   153→- Have `driver.spawn()` throw if the executable is missing\n   154→- Keep a lightweight check in run.ts that asks the driver for its executable path\n   155→\n   156→The simplest approach: let `driver.spawn()` throw with a descriptive error if ralph.sh is missing. run.ts catches the error in its existing try/catch.\n   157→\n   158→### Testing Guidance\n   159→\n   160→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   161→- Import convention: use `.js` extension for ESM resolution.\n   162→- The run.test.ts mock strategy shifts from mocking `node:child_process.spawn` to mocking `agents/index.js.getDriver()`. The mock driver returns a mock `AgentProcess` with controllable stdout/stderr emitters.\n   163→- Test that `handleAgentEvent()` correctly dispatches each `AgentEvent` type to the renderer.\n   164→- Existing tests for `buildSpawnArgs` in `run-helpers.test.ts` and `ralph.test.ts` are NOT affected — they test the ralph module directly.\n   165→\n   166→### Previous Story Intelligence (13-2)\n   167→\n   168→- Story 13-2 completed. `RalphDriver` exists at `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` with `spawn()`, `parseOutput()`, `getStatusFile()`.\n   169→- `RalphDriver.spawn()` currently hardcodes `maxIterations: 50`, `iterationTimeout: 30`, `calls: 100`, `quiet: false`. These need to become configurable (Task 1).\n   170→- `createLineProcessor` in `run-helpers.ts` still imports from `agents/ralph.js` — it's the bridge between old and new patterns.\n   171→- `run.ts` currently re-exports `buildSpawnArgs` and `resolveRalphPath` from line 22. Tests import these from `run.ts`. After migration, tests should import directly from `agents/ralph.js`.\n   172→\n   173→### Project Structure After This Story\n   174→\n   175→```\n   176→src/commands/run.ts              # Refactored: uses AgentDriver interface only\n   177→src/lib/agents/\n   178→├── types.ts                     # AgentDriver, SpawnOpts, AgentProcess, AgentEvent (from 13-1)\n   179→├── ralph.ts                     # RalphDriver with configurable spawn (updated)\n   180→├── stream-parser.ts             # Unchanged (from 13-2)\n   181→├── ralph-prompt.ts              # Unchanged (from 13-2)\n   182→├── index.ts                     # Updated: adds getDriver() factory\n   183→└── __tests__/\n   184→    ├── types.test.ts            # From 13-1\n   185→    ├── ralph.test.ts            # From 13-2\n   186→    ├── stream-parser.test.ts    # From 13-2\n   187→    └── ralph-prompt.test.ts     # From 13-2\n   188→src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts  # Updated: mocks AgentDriver instead of child_process\n   189→src/lib/run-helpers.ts              # Possibly trimmed: createLineProcessor may be removed\n   190→```\n   191→\n   192→### References\n   193→\n   194→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v3.md Decision 3] — Agent Abstraction specification\n   195→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 291-305] — Story 13-3 epic definition\n   196→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types.md] — Story 13-1 completion notes\n   197→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-2-ralph-driver-implementation.md] — Story 13-2 completion notes\n   198→- [Source: src/commands/run.ts] — Primary file to refactor\n   199→- [Source: src/lib/agents/ralph.ts] — RalphDriver implementation to extend\n   200→- [Source: src/lib/agents/index.ts] — Barrel to add getDriver() factory\n   201→- [Source: src/lib/run-helpers.ts] — createLineProcessor to potentially remove\n   202→\n   203→## File List\n   204→\n   205→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Refactor: replace direct spawn/buildSpawnArgs/resolveRalphPath with AgentDriver interface\n   206→- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — Add `getDriver()` factory function\n   207→- `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` — Extend `RalphDriver.spawn()` to accept full configuration\n   208→- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — Possibly add `RalphSpawnOpts` or constructor config type\n   209→- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — Possibly remove `createLineProcessor` if no longer needed\n   210→- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — Update mocks from child_process to AgentDriver\n   211→\n   212→## Change Log\n   213→\n   214→- 2026-03-24: Story created by /create-story\n   215→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ALnzs9UBL7tEMvwMy9zEAC","session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"58a59ccd-1024-49e5-9653-599f650403ef","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:18:34.635Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014q2329hhkDKnT34XrgdzuF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { spawn } from 'node:child_process';\n     2→import { existsSync, mkdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n     3→import { join, dirname } from 'node:path';\n     4→import { Command } from 'commander';\n     5→import { fail, info, jsonOutput } from '../lib/output.js';\n     6→import { readSprintStatusFromState, reconcileState } from '../modules/sprint/index.js';\n     7→import { generateRalphPrompt } from '../lib/agents/ralph-prompt.js';\n     8→import { startRenderer, type SprintInfo } from '../lib/ink-renderer.js';\n     9→import { getSprintState } from '../modules/sprint/index.js';\n    10→import { formatElapsed, mapSprintStatuses, countStories, createLineProcessor } from '../lib/run-helpers.js';\n    11→import { buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath } from '../lib/agents/ralph.js';\n    12→\n    13→// resolveRalphPath moved to src/lib/agents/ralph.ts (story 13-2)\n    14→\n    15→/** Resolves the plugin directory path (.claude/ in project root). */\n    16→export function resolvePluginDir(): string {\n    17→  return join(process.cwd(), '.claude');\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→// Re-export helpers that tests import from run.ts\n    21→export { countStories } from '../lib/run-helpers.js';\n    22→export { buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath } from '../lib/agents/ralph.js';\n    23→\n    24→export function registerRunCommand(program: Command): void {\n    25→  program\n    26→    .command('run')\n    27→    .description('Execute the autonomous coding loop')\n    28→    .option('--max-iterations <n>', 'Maximum loop iterations', '50')\n    29→    .option('--timeout <seconds>', 'Total loop timeout in seconds', '43200')\n    30→    .option('--iteration-timeout <minutes>', 'Per-iteration timeout in minutes', '30')\n    31→    .option('--quiet', 'Suppress terminal output (background mode)', false)\n    32→    .option('--calls <n>', 'Max API calls per hour', '100')\n    33→    .option('--max-story-retries <n>', 'Max retries per story before flagging', '10')\n    34→    .option('--reset', 'Clear retry counters, flagged stories, and circuit breaker before starting', false)\n    35→    .action(async (options, cmd) => {\n    36→      const globalOpts = cmd.optsWithGlobals();\n    37→      const isJson = !!globalOpts.json;\n    38→      const outputOpts = { json: isJson };\n    39→\n    40→      // 1. Resolve Ralph script path\n    41→      const ralphPath = resolveRalphPath();\n    42→      if (!existsSync(ralphPath)) {\n    43→        fail('Ralph loop not found — reinstall codeharness', outputOpts);\n    44→        process.exitCode = 1;\n    45→        return;\n    46→      }\n    47→\n    48→      // 2. Resolve plugin directory\n    49→      const pluginDir = resolvePluginDir();\n    50→      if (!existsSync(pluginDir)) {\n    51→        fail('Plugin directory not found — run codeharness init first', outputOpts);\n    52→        process.exitCode = 1;\n    53→        return;\n    54→      }\n    55→\n    56→      // 2b. Reconcile state (best-effort — failures warn but don't abort)\n    57→      const reconciliation = reconcileState();\n    58→      if (reconciliation.success && reconciliation.data.corrections.length > 0) {\n    59→        for (const correction of reconciliation.data.corrections) {\n    60→          info(`[INFO] Reconciled: ${correction}`, outputOpts);\n    61→        }\n    62→      } else if (!reconciliation.success) {\n    63→        info(`[WARN] State reconciliation failed: ${reconciliation.error}`, outputOpts);\n    64→      }\n    65→\n    66→      // 3. Read sprint status for story count (from sprint-state.json)\n    67→      const projectDir = process.cwd();\n    68→      const sprintStatusPath = join(projectDir, '_bmad-output', 'implementation-artifacts', 'sprint-status.yaml');\n    69→      const statuses = readSprintStatusFromState();\n    70→      const counts = countStories(statuses);\n    71→\n    72→      if (counts.total === 0) {\n    73→        fail('No stories found in sprint-state.json — nothing to execute', outputOpts);\n    74→        process.exitCode = 1;\n    75→        return;\n    76→      }\n    77→\n    78→      info(`Starting autonomous execution — ${counts.ready} ready, ${counts.inProgress} in progress, ${counts.verified} verified, ${counts.done}/${counts.total} done`, outputOpts);\n    79→\n    80→      // 4. Parse and validate numeric options\n    81→      const maxIterations = parseInt(options.maxIterations, 10);\n    82→      const timeout = parseInt(options.timeout, 10);\n    83→      const iterationTimeout = parseInt(options.iterationTimeout, 10);\n    84→      const calls = parseInt(options.calls, 10);\n    85→      const maxStoryRetries = parseInt(options.maxStoryRetries, 10);\n    86→\n    87→      if (isNaN(maxIterations) || isNaN(timeout) || isNaN(iterationTimeout) || isNaN(calls) || isNaN(maxStoryRetries)) {\n    88→        fail('Invalid numeric option — --max-iterations, --timeout, --iteration-timeout, --calls, and --max-story-retries must be numbers', outputOpts);\n    89→        process.exitCode = 1;\n    90→        return;\n    91→      }\n    92→\n    93→      // 5. Generate prompt file (with flagged stories context if available)\n    94→      const promptFile = join(projectDir, 'ralph', '.harness-prompt.md');\n    95→      // Read flagged stories from sprint-state.json (reconcileState may have\n    96→      // already deleted the orphan .flagged_stories file, so read from state)\n    97→      let flaggedStories: string[] | undefined;\n    98→      const flaggedState = getSprintState();\n    99→      if (flaggedState.success && flaggedState.data.flagged?.length > 0) {\n   100→        flaggedStories = flaggedState.data.flagged;\n   101→      }\n   102→      const promptContent = generateRalphPrompt({\n   103→        projectDir,\n   104→        sprintStatusPath,\n   105→        flaggedStories,\n   106→      });\n   107→      try {\n   108→        mkdirSync(dirname(promptFile), { recursive: true });\n   109→        writeFileSync(promptFile, promptContent, 'utf-8');\n   110→      } catch (err) {\n   111→        const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n   112→        fail(`Failed to write prompt file: ${message}`, outputOpts);\n   113→        process.exitCode = 1;\n   114→        return;\n   115→      }\n   116→\n   117→      // 6. Build spawn arguments\n   118→      const args = buildSpawnArgs({\n   119→        ralphPath,\n   120→        pluginDir,\n   121→        promptFile,\n   122→        maxIterations,\n   123→        timeout,\n   124→        iterationTimeout,\n   125→        calls,\n   126→        quiet: options.quiet,\n   127→        maxStoryRetries,\n   128→        reset: options.reset,\n   129→      });\n   130→\n   131→      // 7. Set environment — stream-json is always the output format\n   132→      const env = { ...process.env };\n   133→      if (isJson) {\n   134→        env.CLAUDE_OUTPUT_FORMAT = 'stream-json';\n   135→      }\n   136→\n   137→      // 8. Spawn Ralph — pipe stdout/stderr through stream parser → Ink renderer\n   138→      // Declare renderer handle outside try so cleanup is always reachable\n   139→      const quiet = options.quiet;\n   140→      const rendererHandle = startRenderer({ quiet });\n   141→      let sprintStateInterval: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null;\n   142→      const sessionStartTime = Date.now();\n   143→      let currentIterationCount = 0;\n   144→\n   145→      try {\n   146→        // Read initial sprint state for the renderer header\n   147→        const initialState = getSprintState();\n   148→        if (initialState.success) {\n   149→          const s = initialState.data;\n   150→          const sprintInfo: SprintInfo = {\n   151→            storyKey: s.run.currentStory ?? '',\n   152→            phase: s.run.currentPhase ?? '',\n   153→            done: s.sprint.done,\n   154→            total: s.sprint.total,\n   155→            elapsed: formatElapsed(Date.now() - sessionStartTime),\n   156→            iterationCount: currentIterationCount,\n   157→          };\n   158→          rendererHandle.updateSprintState(sprintInfo);\n   159→        }\n   160→\n   161→        // Feed initial per-story statuses to the renderer\n   162→        const initialStatuses = readSprintStatusFromState();\n   163→        const initialStories = mapSprintStatuses(initialStatuses);\n   164→        if (initialStories.length > 0) {\n   165→          rendererHandle.updateStories(initialStories);\n   166→        }\n   167→\n   168→        const child = spawn('bash', args, {\n   169→          stdio: quiet ? 'ignore' : ['inherit', 'pipe', 'pipe'],\n   170→          cwd: projectDir,\n   171→          env,\n   172→        });\n   173→\n   174→        if (!quiet && child.stdout && child.stderr) {\n   175→          // Wire up stream parser → Ink renderer via extracted createLineProcessor.\n   176→          const stdoutHandler = createLineProcessor({\n   177→            onEvent: (event) => rendererHandle.update(event),\n   178→          });\n   179→          const stderrHandler = createLineProcessor({\n   180→            onEvent: (event) => rendererHandle.update(event),\n   181→            onMessage: (msg) => rendererHandle.addMessage(msg),\n   182→            onIteration: (iteration) => { currentIterationCount = iteration; },\n   183→          }, { parseRalph: true });\n   184→          child.stdout.on('data', stdoutHandler);\n   185→          child.stderr.on('data', stderrHandler);\n   186→\n   187→          // Periodically refresh sprint state for the header display\n   188→          sprintStateInterval = setInterval(() => {\n   189→            try {\n   190→              const stateResult = getSprintState();\n   191→              if (stateResult.success) {\n   192→                const s = stateResult.data;\n   193→                const sprintInfo: SprintInfo = {\n   194→                  storyKey: s.run.currentStory ?? '',\n   195→                  phase: s.run.currentPhase ?? '',\n   196→                  done: s.sprint.done,\n   197→                  total: s.sprint.total,\n   198→                  elapsed: formatElapsed(Date.now() - sessionStartTime),\n   199→                  iterationCount: currentIterationCount,\n   200→                };\n   201→                rendererHandle.updateSprintState(sprintInfo);\n   202→              }\n   203→              // Refresh per-story statuses (AC #7)\n   204→              const currentStatuses = readSprintStatusFromState();\n   205→              const storyEntries = mapSprintStatuses(currentStatuses);\n   206→              rendererHandle.updateStories(storyEntries);\n   207→            } catch {\n   208→              // Ignore read errors during polling\n   209→            }\n   210→          }, 5_000);\n   211→        }\n   212→\n   213→        const exitCode = await new Promise<number>((resolve, reject) => {\n   214→          child.on('error', (err) => {\n   215→            if (sprintStateInterval) clearInterval(sprintStateInterval);\n   216→            rendererHandle.cleanup();\n   217→            reject(err);\n   218→          });\n   219→          child.on('close', (code) => {\n   220→            if (sprintStateInterval) clearInterval(sprintStateInterval);\n   221→            rendererHandle.cleanup();\n   222→            resolve(code ?? 1);\n   223→          });\n   224→        });\n   225→\n   226→        // 9. Handle JSON output on exit\n   227→        if (isJson) {\n   228→          const statusFile = join(projectDir, 'ralph', 'status.json');\n   229→          if (existsSync(statusFile)) {\n   230→            try {\n   231→              const statusData = JSON.parse(readFileSync(statusFile, 'utf-8'));\n   232→              const finalStatuses = readSprintStatusFromState();\n   233→              const finalCounts = countStories(finalStatuses);\n   234→              jsonOutput({\n   235→                status: statusData.status ?? (exitCode === 0 ? 'completed' : 'stopped'),\n   236→                iterations: statusData.loop_count ?? 0,\n   237→                storiesCompleted: finalCounts.done,\n   238→                storiesTotal: finalCounts.total,\n   239→                storiesRemaining: finalCounts.total - finalCounts.done,\n   240→                elapsedSeconds: statusData.elapsed_seconds ?? 0,\n   241→                flaggedStories: statusData.flagged_stories ?? [],\n   242→                exitReason: statusData.exit_reason ?? '',\n   243→              });\n   244→            } catch {\n   245→              jsonOutput({\n   246→                status: exitCode === 0 ? 'completed' : 'stopped',\n   247→                iterations: 0,\n   248→                storiesCompleted: 0,\n   249→                storiesTotal: counts.total,\n   250→                storiesRemaining: counts.total,\n   251→                elapsedSeconds: 0,\n   252→                flaggedStories: [],\n   253→                exitReason: 'status_file_unreadable',\n   254→              });\n   255→            }\n   256→          } else {\n   257→            // status.json not created (Ralph crashed early or never started)\n   258→            const finalStatuses = readSprintStatusFromState();\n   259→            const finalCounts = countStories(finalStatuses);\n   260→            jsonOutput({\n   261→              status: exitCode === 0 ? 'completed' : 'stopped',\n   262→              iterations: 0,\n   263→              storiesCompleted: finalCounts.done,\n   264→              storiesTotal: finalCounts.total,\n   265→              storiesRemaining: finalCounts.total - finalCounts.done,\n   266→              elapsedSeconds: 0,\n   267→              flaggedStories: [],\n   268→              exitReason: 'status_file_missing',\n   269→            });\n   270→          }\n   271→        }\n   272→\n   273→        process.exitCode = exitCode;\n   274→      } catch (err) {\n   275→        if (sprintStateInterval) clearInterval(sprintStateInterval);\n   276→        rendererHandle.cleanup();\n   277→        const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n   278→        fail(`Failed to start Ralph: ${message}`, outputOpts);\n   279→        process.exitCode = 1;\n   280→      }\n   281→    });\n   282→}\n   283→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01ALnzs9UBL7tEMvwMy9zEAC","session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"59c7f70b-9344-4ff1-ae78-5298b2dfbf80","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:18:34.817Z"}
