{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ALnzs9UBL7tEMvwMy9zEAC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here is the summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Story 13-3: Migrate run.ts to Use AgentDriver** -- all 7 tasks completed, story marked for review.\n\n### Files modified:\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` (287 lines) -- Added `RalphConfig` interface and constructor-based configuration. `RalphDriver.spawn()` now reads `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset` from constructor config instead of hardcoded values. Added `existsSync` check inside `spawn()` that throws if ralph.sh is missing.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/index.ts` (55 lines) -- Added `getDriver(name?, config?)` factory function that defaults to `'ralph'` and throws for unknown driver names. Exports `RalphConfig` type.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` (287 lines) -- Full refactor: removed `spawn` from `node:child_process`, removed `buildSpawnArgs`/`resolveRalphPath` imports, removed `createLineProcessor` usage. Now uses `getDriver()` + `driver.spawn()` + `driver.parseOutput()` + `driver.getStatusFile()`. Added `handleAgentEvent()` dispatcher and `createDriverLineHandler()` for line-buffered output processing. Only re-exports `countStories` (not `buildSpawnArgs`/`resolveRalphPath`).\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` (867 lines) -- Rewrote mocks: replaced `node:child_process.spawn` mock with `agents/index.js.getDriver()` mock. Tests now verify `driver.spawn()`, `driver.parseOutput()`, and `driver.getStatusFile()` are called correctly. Added source code verification tests confirming run.ts has no `child_process`, `buildSpawnArgs`, `resolveRalphPath`, or `createLineProcessor` imports. 39 tests pass.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver.md` -- Status changed to `review`, all tasks/subtasks checked.\n\n### Verification:\n- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n- Tests: 136 test files, 3608 tests pass, zero regressions\n- All source files in `src/lib/agents/` and `src/commands/` are under 300 lines\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **AgentEvent-to-StreamEvent type cast**: `handleAgentEvent` casts `AgentEvent` to `StreamEvent` via `as Parameters<RendererHandle['update']>[0]` for the `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `result`, `retry` event types. The two type systems have overlapping shapes but are not formally related. This works because the shapes match structurally, but a future change to either type could silently break the cast. A proper adapter or shared base type would be cleaner.\n\n- **`createLineProcessor` still exists in `run-helpers.ts`**: AC 9 says it can remain as a backward-compatible utility. It's no longer used by `run.ts` but still imports from `agents/ralph.js`. No external consumers were found, so it could be removed in a future cleanup.\n\n- **Single line handler for both stdout and stderr**: The old code used separate handlers (stdout only parsed stream events, stderr parsed both stream events and ralph messages). The new code uses a single `createDriverLineHandler` for both streams, which feeds everything through `driver.parseOutput()`. This is correct because `RalphDriver.parseOutput()` handles both stream-json lines and ralph stderr patterns, but it means stdout lines now also get checked against ralph message patterns (minor unnecessary work, no correctness issue).\n\n- **`storyKey: ''` passed to `driver.spawn()`**: The `SpawnOpts` interface requires `storyKey` but `run.ts` doesn't have a single story key (Ralph picks stories itself). An empty string is passed. This is a mild interface mismatch that could be addressed by making `storyKey` optional in `SpawnOpts`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad8954462f5e70235 (use SendMessage with to: 'ad8954462f5e70235' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 88558\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 438477</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"110312c9-09eb-45d4-bc39-1124b22b5753","uuid":"f88c1d78-a635-450b-b3e7-b43ba001bbf0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:25:48.133Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ad8954462f5e70235","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here is the summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Story 13-3: Migrate run.ts to Use AgentDriver** -- all 7 tasks completed, story marked for review.\n\n### Files modified:\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` (287 lines) -- Added `RalphConfig` interface and constructor-based configuration. `RalphDriver.spawn()` now reads `pluginDir`, `maxIterations`, `iterationTimeout`, `calls`, `quiet`, `maxStoryRetries`, `reset` from constructor config instead of hardcoded values. Added `existsSync` check inside `spawn()` that throws if ralph.sh is missing.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/agents/index.ts` (55 lines) -- Added `getDriver(name?, config?)` factory function that defaults to `'ralph'` and throws for unknown driver names. Exports `RalphConfig` type.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` (287 lines) -- Full refactor: removed `spawn` from `node:child_process`, removed `buildSpawnArgs`/`resolveRalphPath` imports, removed `createLineProcessor` usage. Now uses `getDriver()` + `driver.spawn()` + `driver.parseOutput()` + `driver.getStatusFile()`. Added `handleAgentEvent()` dispatcher and `createDriverLineHandler()` for line-buffered output processing. Only re-exports `countStories` (not `buildSpawnArgs`/`resolveRalphPath`).\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` (867 lines) -- Rewrote mocks: replaced `node:child_process.spawn` mock with `agents/index.js.getDriver()` mock. Tests now verify `driver.spawn()`, `driver.parseOutput()`, and `driver.getStatusFile()` are called correctly. Added source code verification tests confirming run.ts has no `child_process`, `buildSpawnArgs`, `resolveRalphPath`, or `createLineProcessor` imports. 39 tests pass.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver.md` -- Status changed to `review`, all tasks/subtasks checked.\n\n### Verification:\n- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n- Tests: 136 test files, 3608 tests pass, zero regressions\n- All source files in `src/lib/agents/` and `src/commands/` are under 300 lines\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **AgentEvent-to-StreamEvent type cast**: `handleAgentEvent` casts `AgentEvent` to `StreamEvent` via `as Parameters<RendererHandle['update']>[0]` for the `tool-start`, `tool-complete`, `text`, `result`, `retry` event types. The two type systems have overlapping shapes but are not formally related. This works because the shapes match structurally, but a future change to either type could silently break the cast. A proper adapter or shared base type would be cleaner.\n\n- **`createLineProcessor` still exists in `run-helpers.ts`**: AC 9 says it can remain as a backward-compatible utility. It's no longer used by `run.ts` but still imports from `agents/ralph.js`. No external consumers were found, so it could be removed in a future cleanup.\n\n- **Single line handler for both stdout and stderr**: The old code used separate handlers (stdout only parsed stream events, stderr parsed both stream events and ralph messages). The new code uses a single `createDriverLineHandler` for both streams, which feeds everything through `driver.parseOutput()`. This is correct because `RalphDriver.parseOutput()` handles both stream-json lines and ralph stderr patterns, but it means stdout lines now also get checked against ralph message patterns (minor unnecessary work, no correctness issue).\n\n- **`storyKey: ''` passed to `driver.spawn()`**: The `SpawnOpts` interface requires `storyKey` but `run.ts` doesn't have a single story key (Ralph picks stories itself). An empty string is passed. This is a mild interface mismatch that could be addressed by making `storyKey` optional in `SpawnOpts`."}],"totalDurationMs":438477,"totalTokens":88558,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":233,"cache_read_input_tokens":87265,"output_tokens":1059,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":233},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
