{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UdPDEQHzqZ6CtGyjBqM8Ai","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — create-story (2026-03-24T11:34:00Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Epic definition had only 1 AC; expanded to 12 ACs by examining codebase\n     6→- Risk: parseStoryKey() returns [Infinity, Infinity] for non-matching keys — edge case needs handling\n     7→- Risk: orphan file deletion (ACs 3-4) is one-way; must delete AFTER successful state write\n     8→- writeStateAtomic() already calls writeSprintStatusYaml() — reconcileState() may cause double YAML generation\n     9→- retry-state.ts has @deprecated comments saying \"will be removed in story 11-3\" for legacy path helpers\n    10→- run.ts still reads ralph/.flagged_stories directly (line 93-101), bypassing sprint-state.json flagged field — must update before file deletion\n    11→\n    12→### 11-3-state-reconciliation-on-session-start — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:45:00Z)\n    13→\n    14→- Pre-existing ~60 type errors in unrelated test files (not introduced by this story)\n    15→- Readonly mutation workaround: uses JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(...)) deep clone + type assertions to mutate SprintState clone\n    16→- YAML always regenerated even in no-op case — cheap but could be optimized to skip if content unchanged\n    17→\n    18→### 12-1-split-coverage-ts-domain-subdirectory — create-story (2026-03-24T12:01:00Z)\n    19→\n    20→- Workflow file was `workflow.yaml` not `workflow.md` — skill invocation message referenced `.md` but only `.yaml` existed\n    21→- Subagent was instructed not to modify sprint-status.yaml; main agent had to update manually\n    22→- Risk: runner.ts may push past 300 lines if all private helpers are large (~230 line estimate is rough)\n    23→- Risk: AC11 (integration-required) tests e2e CLI behavior identity, requires real project with test runner configured\n    